<subSubSection pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="82.[151,1436,1724,2001]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1765,1791]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[719,743,1766,1791]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles on rear shield margin, directed posteriorly; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae; legs with usual setae, empodium entire; opisthosoma with 5 ridges.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="82.[151,1436,1724,2001]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
This genus consists of 5 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[637,885,1849,1875]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[743,801,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only one species has been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="83" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="82.[151,1436,1724,2001]" lastBlockId="83.[151,1436,158,226]" lastPageId="83" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,329,1932,1958]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Remarks.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roivainen" authorityYear="1951" box="[486,626,1933,1958]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Pentamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[486,626,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Pentamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially introduced by Sowerby, 1813 as a generic name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ozdikmen, H." box="[151,362,1975,2001]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="217 - 230" refId="ref52388" refString="Ozdikmen, H. (2008) Nomenclatural changes for a family group name and twelve genus group names in Acari. Munis Entomology &amp; Zoology, 3, 217 - 230." type="journal article" year="2008">Özdikmen (2008)</bibRefCitation>
noted that 
<taxonomicName authority="Roivainen, 1951" authorityName="Roivainen" authorityYear="1951" box="[506,854,1975,2001]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Pentamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,646,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Pentamerus</emphasis>
Roivainen, 1951
</taxonomicName>
is a junior homonym of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Sowerby, 1813" authorityName="Sowerby" authorityYear="1813" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Pentamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="83" lastPageNumber="84" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1296,1436,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Pentamerus</emphasis>
Sowerby, 1813
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[479,736,158,184]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[581,638,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">et al</emphasis>
. (2003)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Keifer, 1966" authorityName="Keifer" authorityYear="1966" box="[919,1217,158,184]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Echinacrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[919,1053,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Echinacrus</emphasis>
Keifer, 1966
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Roivainen, 1951" authorityName="Roivainen" authorityYear="1951" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Pentamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1296,1436,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Pentamerus</emphasis>
Roivainen, 1951
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Keifer, 1966" authorityName="Keifer" authorityYear="1966" box="[432,720,200,226]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Echinacrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[432,565,200,225]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Echinacrus</emphasis>
Keifer, 1966
</taxonomicName>
is the available name to use.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
